#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Authorization of web endpoints"
msgstr "Web 端点的授权"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Quarkus incorporates a pluggable web security layer.\n"
"When security is active, the system performs a permission check on all HTTP requests to determine if they should proceed."
msgstr "Quarkus 集成了一个可插拔的 Web 安全层。当安全功能处于启用状态时，系统会对所有 HTTP 请求进行权限检查，以确定是否应继续处理这些请求。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Authorization is based on user roles that the security provider provides.\n"
"To customize these roles, a `SecurityIdentityAugmentor` can be created, see\n"
"xref:security-customization.adoc#security-identity-customization[Security Identity Customization]."
msgstr "授权基于安全提供商提供的用户角色。若要自定义这些角色，可以创建 `一个 SecurityIdentityAugmentor` ，请参阅 xref:security-customization.adoc#security-identity-customization[“安全身份自定义”] 。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Authorization using configuration"
msgstr "使用配置进行授权"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "If you work with Jakarta RESTful Web Services (JAX-RS) and need to set default security requirements, consider using <<standard-security-annotations>> and `quarkus.security.jaxrs.deny-unannotated-endpoints` or `quarkus.security.jaxrs.default-roles-allowed` properties instead of the HTTP security policy path-level matching because the security annotations can override these properties on an individual JAX-RS resource or method level."
msgstr "如果您在使用 Jakarta RESTful Web Services（JAX-RS）时需要设置默认安全要求，建议使用 ` <<standard-security-annotations>> ` 以及 ``quarkus.security.jaxrs.deny-unannotated-endpoints` ` 或 ` `quarkus.security.jaxrs.default-roles-allowed` 属性，而不是使用 HTTP 安全策略的路径级匹配，因为安全注解可以在单个 JAX-RS 资源或方法级别覆盖这些属性。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Permissions are defined in the Quarkus configuration by permission sets, each specifying a policy for access control."
msgstr "在 Quarkus 配置中，权限通过权限集进行定义，每个权限集都指定了一条访问控制策略。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "When a security policy's `paths` property contains the most specific path that matches the current request path, it takes precedence over other security policies with matching paths and is said to win."
msgstr "当安全策略的 ``paths`` 属性包含与当前请求路径最匹配的具体路径时，该策略将优先于其他具有匹配路径的安全策略，并被视为“胜出”。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Configured HTTP security policy must not contain a semicolon ';' character in its `paths` property.\n"
"Use <<custom-http-security-policy>> when a security policy decision depends on a presence of certain matrix parameters in the request path."
msgstr "配置的 HTTP 安全策略在其 `paths` 属性中不得包含分号 ';' 字符。当安全策略的决策取决于请求路径中是否存在某些矩阵参数时，请使用 <<custom-http-security-policy>> 。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-authorize-web-endpoints-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Be careful with creating complex, possibly overlapping HTTP security policy path expressions.\n"
"Make sure your HTTP policy configuration is thoroughly tested.\n"
"If you work with Jakarta RESTful Web Services (JAX-RS) and need to create complex security policies, consider using <<standard-security-annotations>> instead."
msgstr "在创建复杂且可能存在重叠的 HTTP 安全策略路径表达式时请务必谨慎。请确保对 HTTP 策略配置进行彻底测试。如果您正在使用 Jakarta RESTful Web Services（JAX-RS）且需要创建复杂的安全策略，建议改用 <<standard-security-annotations>> 。"

